		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://splash247.com/?p=235433</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Amid soaring tanker rates, a US‑led naval coalition has warned shipping that stationary vessels and ships on predictable routes are &#8220;credible&#8221; targets for sabotage across the Middle East, after a tanker linked to the Stena‑Sonangol suezmax pool was struck off the Iraqi coast. The Combined Maritime Forces&#8217; Joint Maritime Information Center (JMIC) advisory underscores that &#8230;</p>
</p>
]]></description>
		
